public struct DataRecord\n{\n    public string StringField1 { get; set; }\n    public string StringField2 { get; set; }\n    public int NumberField1 { get; set; }\n    public double NumberField2 { get; set; }\n}\n\n// Usage\nList<DataRecord> dataRecords = new List<DataRecord>();\n\n// Adding a sample entry\ndataRecords.Add(new DataRecord\n{\n    StringField1 = "Value1",\n    StringField2 = "Value2",\n    NumberField1 = 1,\n    NumberField2 = 2.0\n});\n\n// Example of LINQ usage to filter data\nvar filteredData = dataRecords.Where(d => d.NumberField1 > 0);